Country Demographic Dataset
Loading in the data using API key.

country_names &lt;- unique(cases_year$country)

api_key &lt;- "hmz9wf1cpAko2WM4Fz3oPInaZIt44Uf9uh3VFfxD"

base_url &lt;- "https://api.api-ninjas.com/v1/country"

get_country_demo &lt;- function(country_name){
  GET(url = base_url,
      add_headers('X-API-Key' = api_key),
      query = list(name = country_name)) |&gt;
  content("text", encoding = "utf-8") |&gt;
  fromJSON() |&gt;
  as.data.frame()
}

country_demographic &lt;- map_dfr(country_names, get_country_demo)

Descripion: The Country Demographic Datset is taken from API Ninja’s Country API, which provides geographic, demographic, and economic statistics about every country in the world. Each row represents a single country and each column is a statistic about that country, of which there are 187 countries included and over 40 different statistics.

Visualization 1

library(ggridges)

meta_data |&gt;
  count(country, measles_total) |&gt;
  slice_max(measles_total, n=10) |&gt;
  arrange(desc(n)) |&gt;
  ggplot(aes(x = measles_total,
             y = country,
             fill = country)) +
  geom_density_ridges(alpha = 0.5, scale = 1)
